race.comment: MIDNIGHT STAR (12) comes here third-up and poised to strike after finishing off strongly over this trip at Bunbury last time out. She's had a couple of goes now but she's shown good talent in the process. Will need some things to go her way from the wide alley, but a forward showing is expected back to Country level. EXTRA ZERO (1) sat close to the speed and boxed on strongly over the mile here a fortnight ago. back to 1400m here, though he has placed at this trip on both occasions. Tsang has options from the draw and he can put his best foot forward again. IL BELLO BEALS (2) finished off nicely from the back over 1100m here last start and now jumps straight to 1400m. He ticks a few boxes from a decent alley and he can be in the finish once again. CATERAN (3) gets the blinkers on for the first time today and won't be far away if he runs up to his latest effort. SWISHGOBANGO (10) is one for exotics.
